===subject:Imperalism
===from:Conswella Walker
===email:swellawalker@aol.com
===institution:History 1112
===date:Fri Jun 20 17:07:24 2003
===message:I agree with your statement that there are no justification for imperalism. The term was orginally defined as the domination of European powers-and later United States and Japan as well. Imperalism can also be traced to some of the  major wars and conflicts. Imperalism alone means  "dominance." Dominance can involve a lot of things such as power, money, respect,industralization, and resources. I do not agree with this form of government. Imperalism in my opinion is about power and control. There should be no form of government that have control over an individual's freedom or ideas. This is why imperalism will never prevail. It will never be justifiable because under imperalism power will be the primary goal and the people will be controlled and ruled. Now ask yourself would you like to be ruled or controlled?
=========yorg=========
